The rain began to come down in sheets, not hard, but not a sprinkle. This was a good night she thought. She looked around, giving a call to see who was left to fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#993300>(5/1/03 9:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=201>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Attack Begins</span><hr size=1> Odessa made quick work of two more men who came after her, looking around when the rain started pouring. She was in the midst of another fight after the rain started, knocking the ma unconscious and leaving him for the wolves.<br>
